      "text": [
        "هُ قَالَ لَا تُبَاعُ الصَّدَقَةُ حَتَّى تُعْقَلَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Giyas Bin Ibrahim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Ja’far<sup>asws</sup>, from his<sup>asws</sup> father<sup>asws</sup>, from Ali<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The charity (<span class=\"iTxt\">Zakāt</span>) would not be sold until it is decided upon (for distribution)’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn Yahya from Ghiyath ibn Ibrahim who has said the following: “Ja‘far (abu ‘Abd Allah), ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has narrated from his father from Ali, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, who has said, ‘Charity (Zakat) is not sold before it is received (collected).”’ "
        ]
      }
